## Gating Conditions

A layer, Story Node, scene, or scenario qualifies for the 3D path **only if all required gates pass**.

| # | Condition | Verifiable by |
|---|---|---|
| G-1 | The source artifact is released / published or governed-release-equivalent. | Release register; `PromotionDecision`; `ReleaseManifest` / `MapReleaseManifest`. |
| G-2 | `EvidenceRef` resolution succeeds for any rendered claim. | Governed API resolver; Evidence Drawer parity test. |
| G-3 | Rights, sensitivity, sovereignty, CARE, and public precision policy permit the 3D exposure. | Policy decision; source terms; sensitivity policy; redaction / generalization receipt. |
| G-4 | Vertical, terrain, structural, volumetric, line-of-sight, or globe context materially improves evidence review. | Source descriptor justification; layer / scene manifest; review note. |
| G-5 | A 2D fallback exists and is equally cite-able. | MapLibre layer entry; style / layer manifest; Evidence Drawer test. |
| G-6 | 2D ↔ 3D parity tests are green for this layer / scenario. | `tests/ui/3d_parity/` *(PROPOSED placement)* or repo-native equivalent. |
| G-7 | Performance budget is met, or an explicit reviewed exception is recorded. | Runtime probe; tile load budget; device-tier report; release note. |
| G-8 | Cesium edition / licensing is compatible with the future edition ADR, or exposure is marked `experimental` and non-public. | Edition ADR; package manifest; rights review. |
| G-9 | 3D asset metadata includes digest, source, temporal extent where material, CRS / vertical datum where material, and rollback target. | 3D asset manifest; `TileArtifactManifest`; catalog record. |
| G-10 | Accessibility fallback exists. | 2D fallback, alt text / description metadata, reduced-motion handling where applicable, keyboard Evidence Drawer path. |
| G-11 | Sensitive geometry is transformed before release, not merely hidden by style or camera. | Redaction / generalization receipt; public artifact diff; sensitive-geometry deny fixture. |

A layer that fails **any** of G-1 through G-7 or G-9 through G-11 **MUST NOT** be exposed in the public 3D path. Failure of G-8 reduces the layer to non-public `experimental` exposure until the edition ADR resolves.

