## Conformance

Conformance language follows RFC 2119-style usage.

| ID | Rule | Level |
|---|---|---|
| C-1 | The 2D MapLibre path **MUST** be the default Map Shell surface. | MUST |
| C-2 | Cesium **MUST** read through `apps/governed-api/` and **MUST NOT** read raw, work, quarantine, processed, catalog, graph, model, or runtime stores directly. | MUST |
| C-3 | Cesium **MUST NOT** publish, mutate canonical truth, or write into lifecycle directories. | MUST |
| C-4 | 3D-eligible layers **MUST** carry an explicit evidence-burden justification. | MUST |
| C-5 | Sensitivity, rights, sovereignty, CARE, and Focus Mode constraints **MUST** be enforced identically in 3D and 2D. | MUST |
| C-6 | A 2D ↔ 3D parity test **MUST** pass before a 3D affordance is exposed for a layer / scenario. | MUST |
| C-7 | The Map Shell **MUST** remain functional with Cesium absent, disabled, or build-excluded. | MUST |
| C-8 | `packages/cesium/` **MUST NOT** hard-code a paid-tier Cesium Ion dependency until the edition ADR is accepted. | MUST |
| C-9 | Auto-loading 3D on app entry **MUST NOT** occur. | MUST NOT |
| C-10 | New 3D scene-build workflows **SHOULD** be staged behind a feature flag and accompanied by manifest-bound evidence and receipts. | SHOULD |
| C-11 | Cesium edition spikes **MAY** exist under a clearly marked experimental lane, provided they do not ship to public release. | MAY |
| C-12 | `runtime/` adapters, `connectors/`, `pipelines/`, and `apps/workers/` **MUST NOT** treat Cesium as a sink or as a substitute for catalog closure. | MUST |
| C-13 | 3D assets **MUST** carry digest, source, release, policy, accessibility, and rollback metadata before public exposure. | MUST |
| C-14 | 3D camera paths and animations **SHOULD** include reduced-motion or non-motion alternatives where used in public or semi-public surfaces. | SHOULD |
| C-15 | Public 3D affordances **MUST** show denial, stale, degraded, or abstain states rather than silently hiding failed gates. | MUST |

