## Alternatives Considered

| Alternative | Why considered | Why not chosen |
|---|---|---|
| **A. No 3D at all.** | Simplest. Preserves all invariants by default. | Forfeits legitimate evidence-review value in LiDAR, GLO overlays, terrain, viewshed, hydrology, hazards, archaeology, and volumetric contexts. |
| **B. Cesium as first-class, always-on.** | Makes 3D discoverable from day one. | Violates mobile-first delivery posture, magnifies scene-authoring burden, raises sensitive-geometry risk, and couples release to unresolved edition / licensing. |
| **C. Cesium with a separate API path / store.** | Could optimize 3D-specific delivery. | Direct violation of the trust membrane; creates parallel authority. |
| **D. Cesium behind the governed API, but no parity contract.** | Lower test burden. | Allows 2D and 3D to disagree about shown, cited, denied, or stale content. |
| **E. Pin Cesium Ion now.** | Operationally convenient. | Pre-empts edition / licensing review and creates rollback debt. |
| **F. (Chosen) Cesium 3D as conditional, opt-in, evidence-gated.** | Preserves invariants while admitting evidence-bearing 3D use. | Requires additional manifests, gates, tests, and follow-up ADRs. |

